{
  "0": "Recurrent Neural Network (RNN): The",
  "1": "Recurrent Neural Network is a",
  "2": "foundational architecture that preceded",
  "3": "the Transformer. RNNs process",
  "4": "information sequentially, using loops to",
  "5": "maintain a \"memory\" of previous inputs,",
  "6": "which made them suitable for tasks like",
  "7": "text and speech processing.",
  "8": "Mixture of Experts (MoE): Mixture of",
  "9": "Experts is an efficient model architecture",
  "10": "where a \"router\" network dynamically",
  "11": "selects a small subset of \"expert\"",
  "12": "networks to handle any given input. This",
  "13": "allows models to have a massive",
  "14": "number of parameters while keeping",
  "15": "computational costs manageable.",
  "16": "5"
}